semble est cependant mise au défi dans le contexte actuel caractérisé par la multiplication des porte-paroles et les questionnements d’inclusion identitaire.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAcadianszNew BrunswickxHistory. 0aAcadianszNew BrunswickxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311127402708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2015z978311127703540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978276372341940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782763723419423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9782763723419/original  a978-3-11-127402-7  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-127703-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles